<p>Try this <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">for-else</code> tip</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>needle = 'd'
haystack = ['a', 'b', 'c']

#Bad example

found = False
for letter in haystack:
    if needle == letter:
        print('Found')
        found = True
        break
if not found:
    print('Not found')

#### Better example

for letter in haystack:
    if needle == letter:
        print('Found')
        break
else: # if no break found:
    print('Not found')
</code></pre></div></div>

